\v 3 Starting a new verse. You can hit Alt-downarrow to go to the next verse. This does skip to the next verse when typing at the end of the verse. A work-around for using the browser is to put several characters at the end of the verse. So right now I am typing without the right column switching places, because the three dollar signs are at the end of the verse. $$$
\v 4 So with the dollar signs at the end, and typing before them, the editor doesn't skip around. $$$
